\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. CERATOCHLOA (Beauv.) Griseb. Short-lived perennials. Spikelets ovate or ovate-lanceolate, strongly compressed. Lower glume 3- to 5-veined, the upper 5- to 7-veined. Lemma and glumes strongly keeled on the back. Awn usually much shorter than the lemma, often absent.
