\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. BRACHYPODIUM (incl.{\i  Brevipodium} A. & D. Löve, {\i Leptorachis} Nevski). Perennials. Leaves flat or convolute, flaccid or rigid. Raceme usually elongate and nodding or drooping. Spikelets terete or subterete, rarely fewer than 5. Glumes and lemmas chartaceous. Anthers at least 2·5 mm.
