\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. B. pinnatum} (L.) Beauv.,{\i  Agrost}. 101, 155 (1812). Rhizomatous, sometimes subcaespitose; stems 40-120 cm, erect, pubescent at the nodes. Leaves 10-40 cm × 3-6(-8) mm, flat or somewhat convolute, sparsely hairy on the upper surface, scabrid beneath; ligule c. 2 mm, truncate. Raceme 7-20 cm, erect, with up to 15 spikelets. Spikelets terete, linear, somewhat patent especially before maturity, with 8-24 florets. Lower glume 3-6 mm, the upper 5-8 mm. Lemma oblong-lanceolate; awn erect. Anthers 3·5-5·5 mm. 2n = 14, 16, 28.{\i  Dry grassland and woods; usually calcicole. Europe, northwards to} 62° 30' {\i in N.W. Russia.} All except Az Bl Fa Is Sb.
